{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Giacomo Debidda","author":"Giacomo Debidda","description":"Giacomo Debidda's Personal Blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"8bbd59ec-78b8-59d9-b518-9498cf4bec2f","excerpt":"Last month I gave a talk at  PyMunich  on how to create reactive dashboards with Plotly  Dash . I have already written about Dash  here…","timeToRead":1,"html":"<p>Last month I gave a talk at <a href=\"https://www.meetup.com/it-IT/PyMunich/\">PyMunich</a> on how to create reactive dashboards with Plotly <a href=\"https://plot.ly/products/dash/\">Dash</a>.</p>\n<p>I have already written about Dash <a href=\"https://www.giacomodebidda.com/visualize-earthquakes-with-plotly-dash/\">here</a>, and the weekend before the presentation I managed to deploy <a href=\"https://github.com/jackdbd/dash-fda\">another dashboard</a> on <a href=\"https://mighty-garden-67470.herokuapp.com/\">Heroku</a>.</p>\n<p>It seems that the audience liked the topic, and on Twitter <a href=\"https://github.com/chriddyp\">Chris Parmer</a> himself wrote some kind words of appreciation. I wasn’t expecting that. It was pretty cool!</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-5b410.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 34.01253918495298%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Chris Parmer's Tweet\"\n        title=\"Chris Parmer's Tweet\"\n        src=\"/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-fb8a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/tweet-chrisp-72b1de08c98b8906f192b7c05805bd6c-5b410.png 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Dash is a pretty new framework in the Python ecosystem, but I think it will manage to get its own space among tools like Jupyter noteboooks and Bokeh interactive plots.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ucg8j\">Luke Singham</a> started <a href=\"https://github.com/Acrotrend/awesome-dash\">awesome-dash</a>, a curated list of awesome Dash resources. It contains links to tutorials, code snippets, example dashboards that will definitely be useful if you are just starting with Dash or want to learn a new thing or two. Don’t forget to start it on GitHub!</p>\n<p>Here are the slides of my talk:</p>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 72.91666666666666%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe src=\"//slides.com/jackdbd/deck/embed\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" allowfullscreen style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Reactive Dashboards with Plotly Dash","date":"December 10, 2017"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/reactive-dashboards-with-plotly-dash/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-get-started-with-regl-and-webpack/"},"timeToRead":18,"frontmatter":{"title":"How to get started with regl and Webpack","path":"/how-to-get-started-with-regl-and-webpack/"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/interesting-things-other-people-did-in-2017/"},"timeToRead":5,"frontmatter":{"title":"Interesting things other people did in 2017","path":"/interesting-things-other-people-did-in-2017/"}}}}